I  am  the  stuckee  at the PMO who is going to have to advise my
bosses on an approach for MILNET naming.  One I've discussed with
the  NIC  and  with the IETF people working with DOMAIN naming is
the following.

1. Establish N.MIL, AF.MIL, A.MIL  and  MC.MIL  as  second  level
domains.   Joint  and Specified agencies/commands also get second
level domains.

2. If you would logically fit under one  of  the  upperlevel  (in
NPRDCs case the N.MIL) domains, you have to get approval from the
owner of that doamin to establish your own second  level  domain.
I.e.   if  you  can convince the NAVY agency that is handling DDN
issues (NAVDAC?)  you can have your own domain.

This is DRAFT only and for discussion and not  implementation  at
this time.


Capt.  Mike StJohns, B612, DDN PMO

